ame, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705185,"age":6,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Henry de Stanley of Stoneleigh was born from 1100 to 1199, in Balterley, Staffordshire, England as the son of Robert de Stonlegh Sheriff. He had at least 1 daughter. He died in 1117, in England."},"et":{"from 1100 to 1199–1117":"1100 kuni 1199–1117","1100–1117":"1100–1117","1114–Female":"1114–Surnud","1067–Male":"1067–Surnud","1117":"1117","1106":"1106","1114":"1114","1067":"1067","1100":"1100","from 1100 to 1199":"1100 kuni 1199","Stoneley Balterley, Staffordshire, England":"Balterley, Staffordshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"England"},"fi":{"from 1100 to 1199–1117":"vuodesta 1100 vuoteen 1199–1117","1100–1117":"1100–1117","1114–Female":"1114–Kuollut","1067–Male":"1067–Kuollut","1117":"1117","1106":"1106","1114":"1114","1067":"1067","1100":"1100","from 1100 to 1199":"vuodesta 1100 vuoteen 1199","Stoneley Balterley, Staffordshire, England":"Balterley, Staffordshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"England"},"fr":{"from 1100 to 1199–1117":"du 1100 au 1199–1117","1100–1117":"1100–1117","1114–Female":"1114–Décédée","1067–Male":"1067–Décédé","1117":"1117","1106":"1106","1114":"1114","1067":"1067","1100":"1100","from 1100 to 1199":"du 1100 au 1199","Stoneley Balterley, Staffordshire, England":"Balterley, Staffordshire, Angleterre","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Henry de Stanley of Stoneleigh est n